org.apache.jena.fuseki.servlets

Class HttpAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.jena.fuseki.servlets.HttpAction

  • public class HttpAction
extends Object
    HTTP action that represents the user request lifecycle. Its state is handled in the ActionSPARQL.executeAction(HttpAction) method.

    • Method Detail

      • setRequest

        public void setRequest(DataAccessPoint dataAccessPoint,
                       DataService dService)
        Initialization after action creation during lifecycle setup.

        Sets the action dataset. Setting will replace any existing DataAccessPoint and DataService, as the DatasetGraph of the current HTTP Action.

        Once it has updated its members, the HTTP Action will change its transactional state and Transactional instance according to its base dataset graph.

        Parameters:
        dataAccessPoint - DataAccessPoint
        dService - DataService
        See Also:
        Transactional
